00:12:33.410 --> 00:12:35.820
JOHN DAY-RICHTER: So the Drive
SDK also has some great

00:12:35.820 --> 00:12:36.920
security features.

00:12:36.920 --> 00:12:41.660
And we found that users are more
likely to use apps that

00:12:41.660 --> 00:12:44.460
they trust, so if you have a
very scary security warning

00:12:44.460 --> 00:12:47.010
when your app is installed,
users often walk

00:12:47.010 --> 00:12:48.070
away at that point.

00:12:48.070 --> 00:12:51.370
We've done everything we can
to make sure that your app

00:12:51.370 --> 00:12:54.550
gets at the data that it needs,
but only the data that

00:12:54.550 --> 00:12:58.070
it needs so that users aren't
scared off and there's less of

00:12:58.070 --> 00:13:02.000
a danger of a user installing
an app that misbehaves.

00:13:02.000 --> 00:13:07.290
So many people have asked, can
I do this thing with the

00:13:07.290 --> 00:13:09.270
Google Drive SDK version one?

00:13:09.270 --> 00:13:12.540
And I will say, no, you can't
do that, and they will say,

00:13:12.540 --> 00:13:13.410
are you lazy?

00:13:13.410 --> 00:13:15.460
And I will say, yes,
but that's not it,

00:13:15.460 --> 00:13:16.640
it's actually a feature.

00:13:16.640 --> 00:13:22.030
So with Drive apps in the SDK
version one, apps can only

00:13:22.030 --> 00:13:25.270
access files that the app
created, or that the user

00:13:25.270 --> 00:13:27.100
explicitly gave access to.

00:13:27.100 --> 00:13:31.970
So if a user's installed your
app, your app still can't get

00:13:31.970 --> 00:13:35.420
at their files until they choose
to open the file with

00:13:35.420 --> 00:13:38.620
your app in Google Drive, and
that way if the user installs

00:13:38.620 --> 00:13:41.960
an evil app, it's still only
being evil at one or two

00:13:41.960 --> 00:13:45.350
files, and it's very easy in
the Google Drive UI to

00:13:45.350 --> 00:13:49.110
uninstall apps and revoke
access to files for a

00:13:49.110 --> 00:13:51.840
particular app if a user feels
like it's misbehaving.

00:13:51.840 --> 00:13:54.900
And all of this is bringing
great peace of mind to our

00:13:54.900 --> 00:13:57.910
suspicious web users.

00:13:57.910 --> 00:14:00.450
