from Google, so it's in

00:14:16.640 --> 00:14:19.640
a trusted context from Google,
they choose the files that

00:14:19.640 --> 00:14:22.910
they want to open with your app,
the picker grants access

00:14:22.910 --> 00:14:25.220
to your app when the user
chooses it, and then your app

00:14:25.220 --> 00:14:26.280
has access to the file.

00:14:26.280 --> 00:14:30.450
So you can still make apps that
operate on any arbitrary

00:14:30.450 --> 00:14:34.670
file in the user's corpus,
and it's very secure.

